The Ndlovu Choir has been making Mzansi proud at America's Got Talent competition and they are ready to come back home. The whole of Mzansi has rallied behind the choir since they sung their way into the finale. The Minister of Arts And Culture Nathi Mthethwa also posted a message of support to the group, wishing them well for their future endevours. He tweeted: "There's no doubt that one of the greatest highlights of 2019 has been the outstanding contribution @ChoirAfrica has made in representing our country on @AGT. We wish you all the best for your finale tonight. We are behind you, go out there & shine". 